																								<h5 class="card-head flow-text"><a class="grey-text text-darken-4 " href="https://iapp.org/news/a/what-does-the-convention-108-mean-for-uk-adequacy/">What does the 'Convention 108+' mean for UK adequacy?</a></h5>
																																																															<div class="card-body">
																	An overhauled Convention 108 was signed by 20 states â including the U.K. â in early October. The Council of Europe treaty has been given an update to bring it in line with the EU General Data Protection Regulation. The European Commission sees the protocol as a way of encouraging "third countries" ...
								 
